# pmGPT — Cursor Project Rules

## CRITICAL: Read these files before writing any code
- `MASTER_PLAN.md` — 259-task build plan. Always check task status (✅/🔧/❌) before building anything
- `CLAUDE.md` — Full codebase context, design system, API map, dos/don'ts
- `HANDOFF.md` — What was last worked on and what's next

---

## What This Product Is

pmGPT is a **Product Management OS** — AI-native workspace for PMs, PM Leads, and founders at B2B SaaS companies.

**North star:** One person + pmGPT = a full product team.

**ICP:** Founders acting as de facto PM (pre-Series B), Head of Product at lean companies, solo PMs doing the work of 3-person teams.

**Core interaction model:** Alert → Investigate → Preview → Approve → Execute.
Agents NEVER act unilaterally. Every write action (Jira, Notion, Slack) requires human preview + approval first.

---

## Monorepo Structure

```
pmgpt/
├── onboarding/        # Next.js 14 frontend (App Router, TypeScript)
├── backend/           # FastAPI Python backend
├── MASTER_PLAN.md     # 259-task roadmap — source of truth for what to build
├── CLAUDE.md          # Full codebase context
├── HANDOFF.md         # Session handoff state
└── docs/
    ├── DESIGN_SYSTEM.md
    └── ARCHITECTURE.md
```

---

## Tech Stack

**Frontend** (`onboarding/`)
- Next.js 14 App Router, TypeScript strict
- Tailwind CSS with custom brand tokens (see brand system below — NEVER use raw colors)
- No shadcn/ui except Button primitive
- State: React useState/useEffect only (no Redux, no Zustand)
- Auth: localStorage JWT (temporary — real auth is Section 1 of MASTER_PLAN)
- API: `onboarding/lib/api.ts` — all calls go through `req()` wrapper

**Backend** (`backend/`)
- FastAPI + Uvicorn, async
- DB: SQLite + SQLAlchemy 2.0 (PostgreSQL + Alembic planned — see Section 1.2 of MASTER_PLAN)
- LLM routing: Claude (Opus/Sonnet/Haiku), GPT-4o, Gemini, Mistral local
- RAG: vector store per connector, retrieval before every agent call
- Auth: JWT middleware, RBAC: viewer / pm / pm_lead / admin

---

## Brand Token System (ALWAYS use these — never raw Tailwind colors)

```
bg-brand-bg / bg-brand-bg-2         # page background / elevated background
bg-brand-surface                     # card/panel surface
bg-brand-elevated                    # hover states
bg-brand-canvas                      # input backgrounds
bg-brand-sidebar                     # left nav
bg-brand-accent                      # primary action (purple-ish) — use sparingly
bg-brand-accent-bg / bg-brand-accent-dim

text-brand-ink                       # primary text
text-brand-ink-2 / -3 / -4           # secondary / tertiary / disabled
text-brand-ink-inv / -inv-2          # text on dark backgrounds
text-brand-accent-text

border-brand-line / border-brand-line-2

bg-brand-green / -amber / -red       # success / warning / error
text-brand-green / -amber / -red
bg-brand-green-bg / -amber-bg / -red-bg
```

